  "body": "I am running Erigon with the following settings:\r\n`--chain=bsc --datadir=/data/erigon-bsc/node --prune=hrtc`\r\nThe current stage has already been running for 3 days straight, and it barely got halfway:\r\n`INFO[01-29|10:07:19.170] [5/15 Execution] Executed blocks         number=7664467 blk/s=5.205 tx/s=1836.131 Mgas/s=303.532 batch=\"308.55 MiB\" alloc=\"1.46 GiB\" sys=\"17.30 GiB\"`\r\n\r\nThe machine is a 32-core AMD, 128Gb RAM and 4TB NVMe SSD, which is more than able to sync and run BSC + Geth in under 2 days.\r\n\r\nCould the sync process be accelerated?",
